//Project Title
A short, one-sentence description of your project and what it does.

//Technologies Used
Frontend: React, Tailwind CSS

Backend: Node.js, Express.js

Database: MongoDB (I used MongoDB because I am more familiar and comfortable with it, which allowed me to develop the project more efficiently and deliver the features more quickly.)

Authentication: Cookie-based sessions for secure and stateful user authentication.

//Features
List the main functionalities of your application.

User Authentication: Secure login, signup, and logout for different roles (Admin, Store Owner, User).

Role-Based Access Control: Restricts access to certain pages and features based on the user's role.

Admin Dashboard: Allows admins to create new users and assign stores to them.

Store Owner Dashboard: Enables store owners to view their store details and manage ratings.

Password Management: Users can change their password after logging in.

How to Run Locally
Follow these steps to get the project running on your local machine.

//Backend Setup
Navigate to the backend directory: cd backend
 Install dependencies: npm install

Set up your MongoDB connection string in a .env file.
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string

Run the server: npm start

// Frontend Setup
Navigate to the frontend directory: cd frontend

Install dependencies: npm install

Run the client: npm run dev

Your application should now be running on http://localhost:5173 (or the port specified in your console).